ycle taxi drivers in Bangkok. Claudio Sopranzetti advances an analysis of power that focuses not on the sturdiness of hegemony or the ubiquity of everyday resistance but on its potential fragility and the work needed for its maintenance.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh  a2010 bangkok protests.  a21st century thai economics.  a21st century thai inequality.  a21st century thailand.  abangkok protests.  acontemporary political mobilizations in thailand.  ademocratizing thailand.  aeconomy in thailand.  aeveryday resistance in thailand.  alabor class politics in thailand.  amotorcycle taxis in thailand.  aprotestors in thailand.  arevolution.  astate power in bangkok.  astate power in thailand.  athai economy.  athai protest.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831106675540 cprintz978052028850840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780520963399?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520963399423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520963399/original  a978-3-11-066755-4  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY